Orange Fox Security spokesperson Marc Bester said three suspects broke into a business in Centurion near Pretoria this past Sunday morning, the Centurion Rekord reports. Bester said Monitornet was first on the scene and caught the robbers in the act. When the alarm went off, Monitornet was the first to arrive on the scene and immediately caught the first suspect, said Bester. The other suspects attempted to escape and jumped over the wall, but with the help of the CPF and Metro police, the other two suspects were caught. READ MORE: Watch: Durban bank robbery caught on camera Stolen equipment from the business was retrieved after the suspects were detained. Bester thanked all the parties involved for their good teamwork. &#8211; Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.